[SN]TITLE[SN]
2017 Island Games: Jersey name shooting team for Gotland

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Jersey has named an 18-strong shooting team for this summer's Island Games.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Reigning smallbore 100-yard prone champion Andy Chapman is part of five smallbore shooters.
Veteran air rifle shooter David Turner is picked alongside Jonathan Bouchard while 2015 fullbore team gold medallist Bruce Horwood is also going to Gotland.
2015 pistol gold medallist James Daly is joined by experienced pistol veterans Mick Radcliffe, Mary Norman and Michael Quenault.
Jersey's shooters won 20 gold medals at the last Island Games - 40% of all of the golds won by the island.
Jersey team: Steve Bouchard, Andy Chapman, Sarah Campion, Sue de Gruchy, Craig Marett, David Turner, Jonathan Bouchard, Debbie Thompson, Bruce Horwood, Gregory Guida, Amy Hall, Michael Quenault, Mary Norman, Mick Radcliffe, Alain Cabaret, Tobias Cabaret, James Daly, Mike Nolan.
